%mbx script removed problem header Use a graph to estimate the limit \[\lim_{\theta \rightarrow 0} \frac{\sin(9\theta)}{\theta}.\] Note: \(\theta\) is measured in radians. All angles will be in radians in this class unless otherwise specified.
\par \(\lim\limits_{\theta \rightarrow 0} \frac{\sin(9\theta)}{\theta} =\) \mbox{\parbox[t]{17.5ex}{\hrulefill}}
\par \par {\bf Solution: }\par SOLUTION \par
For \(-\frac12\leq\theta\leq \frac12\), \(-1\leq y\leq 10\), the graph of \(\frac{\sin(9\theta)}{\theta}\) is shown below. \par \begin{center} \includegraphics[width=0.5\linewidth]{webwork-tex/webwork-8-image-1.png}
\end{center} \par Therefore, \[\lim_{\theta \rightarrow 0} \frac{\sin(9\theta)}{\theta} = 9.\]
\par
